<div class="beta-hero">
  <h1>Beta Calculator</h1>
  <p class="subtitle">Calculate stock beta from returns data, estimate beta quickly, and compute weighted portfolio beta. Understand the beta coefficient and how to use it in the CAPM model.</p>
</div>

<div class="beta-container">

  <!-- Stat Cards -->
  <div class="stat-row">
    <div class="stat-card"><div class="stat-value">1.00</div><div class="stat-label">S&P 500 Beta</div></div>
    <div class="stat-card"><div class="stat-value">~1.2</div><div class="stat-label">Avg Tech Sector Beta</div></div>
    <div class="stat-card"><div class="stat-value">~0.4</div><div class="stat-label">Avg Utilities Beta</div></div>
    <div class="stat-card"><div class="stat-value">36-60</div><div class="stat-label">Months Used Typically</div></div>
  </div>

  <!-- ============ STOCK BETA CALCULATOR ============ -->
  <h2 class="section-title" id="stock-beta-calculator">Stock Beta Calculator</h2>
  <p class="section-desc">Enter comma-separated monthly returns for both the stock and the market index (e.g., S&P 500). The calculator computes beta using covariance/variance, plus R-squared and Jensen's alpha.</p>

  <div class="calc-grid">
    <div class="calc-panel">
      <h3>📈 Returns Data</h3>
